description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for this notable post of All-Wales Adult Metabolic Dietitian / UHW Operational Lead Dietitian. The post holder will work alongside the All-Wales strategic Dietetic lead with a clinical remit for Adult Inherited Metabolic Disease (IMD), based in the Cardiff and Vale hub. This post will share responsibility for delivery of dietetic service provision across Wales; both in acute and outpatient settings. You will work collaboratively with the wider IMD multi-disciplinary team. The successful candidate, along with three other postholders, provide operational leadership for the adult acute based dietetic team on site responsible for staff management, supervision and staff development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require substantial clinical dietetic experience in an acute hospital setting in a specialised area of dietetics e.g. gastroenterology, renal, hepatology, diabetes, &lt;strong&gt;or&lt;/strong&gt; experience in general adult dietetics including clinical dietetic experience with IMD. Previous experience of people management and evidence of leadership is also desirable. You will demonstrate excellent interpersonal skills with a practical, forward thinking approach to service development and evaluation. Motivational interviewing skills are desirable to work with this client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent career opportunity for a dietitian with IMD experience or significant acute specialised experience who would like to further develop their clinical and strategic and management skills of service and policy development. The post holder will report to the Head of Dietetic Services for the Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within a friendly, dynamic, large secondary and tertiary care department at the University Hospital of Wales. Numerous opportunities for professional and personal development will be available to you. The service has aspires to ensure all staff in a leadership position have had the opportunity to develop leadership skills through training and education. You will be actively involved in the research, audit, service development and the Clinical Governance agenda. We are committed to the training of student dietitians and are actively involved in the supporting other members of the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate that they share our organisational values:&lt;br /&gt;- We care about each other&lt;br /&gt;- We trust one another&lt;br /&gt;- We respect each other&lt;br /&gt;- We take personal responsibility &lt;br /&gt;- We treat people with kindness&lt;br /&gt;- We act with integrity&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Post holders will be expected at all times to behave in accordance with our values demonstrating commitment to the delivery of high quality services to patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable but not essential for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sarah Bailey Job title Operational Lead Dietitian&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address sarah.bailey3@wales.nhs.uk Telephone number 02921844294&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Bailey or Claire Constantinou&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 029 2184 4294&lt;/p&gt;
